aa(lp239
VNow with all this beauty, usefulness and wealth,
p240
aVmathematics does look more sexy.
p241
aVBut don't you think
p242
aVthat the life a mathematical researcher is an easy one.
p243
aVIt is filled with perplexity,
p244
aVfrustration,
p245
aVa desperate fight for understanding.
p246
aa(lp247
VLet me evoke for you
p248
aVone of the most striking days in my mathematician's life.
p249
aVOr should I say,
p250
aVone of the most striking nights.
p251
aVAt that time,
p252
aVI was staying at the Institute for Advanced Studies in Princeton \u2014
p253
aVfor many years, the home of Albert Einstein
p254
aVand arguably the most holy place for mathematical research in the world.
p255
aVAnd that night I was working and working on an elusive proof,
p256
aVwhich was incomplete.
p257
aVIt was all about understanding
p258
aVthe paradoxical stability property of plasmas,
p259
aVwhich are a crowd of electrons.
p260
aVIn the perfect world of plasma,
p261
aVthere are no collisions
p262
aVand no friction to provide the stability like we are used to.
p263
aVBut still,
p264
aVif you slightly perturb a plasma equilibrium,
p265
aVyou will find that the resulting electric field
p266
aVspontaneously vanishes,
p267
aVor damps out,
p268
aVas if by some mysterious friction force.
p269
aa(lp270
VThis paradoxical effect,
p271
aVcalled the Landau damping,
p272
aVis one of the most important in plasma physics,
p273
aVand it was discovered through mathematical ideas.
p274
aVBut still,
p275
aVa full mathematical understanding of this phenomenon was missing.
p276
aVAnd together with my former student and main collaborator Clément Mouhot,
p277
aVin Paris at the time,
p278
aVwe had been working for months and months on such a proof.
p279
aVActually,
p280
aVI had already announced by mistake that we could solve it.
p281
aVBut the truth is,
p282
aVthe proof was just not working.
p283
aVIn spite of more than 100 pages of complicated, mathematical arguments,
p284
aVand a bunch discoveries,
p285
aVand huge calculation,
p286
aVit was not working.
p287
aVAnd that night in Princeton,
p288
aVa certain gap in the chain of arguments was driving me crazy.
p289
aVI was putting in there all my energy and experience and tricks,
p290
aVand still nothing was working.
p291
aV1 a.m., 2 a.m., 3 a.m.,
p292
aVnot working.
p293
aVAround 4 a.m., I go to bed in low spirits.
p294
aVThen a few hours later,
p295
aVwaking up and go,
p296
aV"Ah, it's time to get the kids to school \u2014"
p297
aVWhat is this?
p298
aVThere was this voice in my head, I swear.
p299
aV"Take the second term to the other side,
p300
aVFourier transform and invert in L2."
p301
aa(lp302
V(Laughter)
p303
aa(lp304
VDamn it,
p305
aVthat was the start of the solution!
p306
aa(lp307
VYou see,
p308
aVI thought I had taken some rest,
p309
aVbut really my brain had continued to work on it.
p310
aVIn those moments,
p311
aVyou don't think of your career or your colleagues,
p312
aVit's just a complete battle between the problem and you.
